g.text: Savoir Faire: Pier? Buildings? Apartments? You should *explore*, maybe scale a wall?
The Gardener: "An autopsy? Wow. Sure, keep them." She hands you the rubber gloves. "I have another pair."
You: "It's not in the yard anymore. It's in... some other place now."

You: "There's more to you than that."
The Gardener: "I'm okay with it. Was there something else?"
Empathy: She doesn't like that *giant* boat. Nor does she like the woman on it.
The Gardener: "I don't know... the abandoned kind? It used to gather every spring, but there's nothing to do there now. Just drug addicts."
The Gardener: "A bit much? What are you talking about? That's what my grandma told me, okay?"
Empathy: She would probably prefer not to go into it. It wasn't easy to pick up on either...
Shivers: Rows of stalls under a broad roof, where silvery fish were heaped on newspapers. Water, water everywhere -- pouring from the heavens, in the shadow of the old church.
The Gardener: "Anything else?" The girl watches you rub your sides for warmth.
The Gardener: "I have a greenhouse in the yard there." She gestures over her shoulder. "I've been trying to get some work done..."
"I have a greenhouse in the yard there." She gestures over her shoulder.
You: "Cool. And what are you doing here?"
The Gardener: "Sure, keep them. I have another pair." She hands you the rubber gloves with no visible annoyance.
"Since the street sign's messed up..." She nods. "Okay. What do you need?"
You: "I didn't say you wrote it."
You: "I'm... disorientated. I don't know where I am."
"I'm a bit disoriented. This is Revachol, right?"
Drama: Surely it was nothing, sire. Just paranoia.
You: Why am I thinking this, I said I'm black as fuck.
Half Light: Really? *None.* Maybe just a *tiny* bit of annoyance.
You: "Nothing, this is just something my brain told me."
You: "It's so late and you're still here."

Composure: She's very well composed. Back straight.
Empathy: There's discomfort. She stops mid sentence.
You: "Can I borrow your gloves? I'm doing an autopsy."
You: So what? I'm also black.

You: No. I don't want to say that.
You: "It was sent to processing in the morgue."
You: I don't care, I just wanna enjoy the nice moment.
Drama: Of course, sire, of course.

Authority: Nothing to see here. Just a regular law official reacting to every day stimuli. Nothing noteworthy here.
You: "It's alright, I didn't mean to startle you."

Encyclopedia: *Pig* is a widely-used term for members of the Police. It's not loving.

You: An entrance to the yard?

Kim Kitsuragi: "Don't worry, miss. We're here to clean it up -- you can get to work soon."
The Gardener: "We don't see a lot of police around here, that's all."
The Gardener: "Me? I'm just a gardener."
Composure: She hides it well, but behind the sweat and dirt there is something... else. In her rigid posture.
Interfacing: Those gloves would really come in handy for the autopsy.
The Gardener: "Can you tell me when you've taken him away then. Because I'm sort of waiting for *that*."
The Gardener: "Sure -- I'm done with them." She takes a small capsule out of her breast pocket and hands it to you.
You: Yeah, I'm not gonna say that.
The Gardener: "It is, because he sent you to harass me, didn't he? You shouldn't listen to him." She points to the defaced sign above her on the corner. "It was probably him, who wrote that."
You: "I was talking to him, yes."
The Gardener: "Oh. Okay." She doesn't quite know what to say. "Thanks for keeping me in the know, sir."
The Gardener: "The RCM in Martinaise?" The young woman looks up at you. "What can I help you with?"
The Gardener: "Of course. What can I help you with?"
The Gardener: "Of course, I won't hold you back." She wipes her brow with the canary yellow glove.
The Gardener: "There's the pier, the Capeside apartment buildings. Some more tenements... Not a lot, really."
You: "What is on the other side of the canal?"
Conceptualization: Yeah, keep her in the *loop*. It's strangely enjoyable to report back on the minute progress you've made. Even to strangers.
The Gardener: "I'm a night hawk, what can I say?" She flashes a smile.
The Gardener: "I like the city at night. Don't you?" She looks into the darkness and smiles again.
Drama: There's a little meanness in that smile.
You: "What about the other sign. *Pigs go home*? Who are these pigs?"
Perception (Smell): Even all the way over here, there's a drop of death in the spring air.
Kim Kitsuragi: "No need to worry," the lieutenant steps in, "we're not saying you did."
The Gardener: "Well uh..." She points to her wheelbarrow, surprised at the question. "This might be the last snow we get. At least I hope so..."
You: Shake it off, you seem to be under some kind of cold spell...
You: "I have some questions for you."
The Gardener: "It's raining again..." The young woman resting by the wheelbarrow sighs.
"It's raining again..." The young woman looks up at the overladen sky.
You: "Do you still have your salts? I think I could use some."
The Gardener: "No problem." She nods, brushing a fleck of soil off her cheek.
You: "My partner told me you may have ammonia -- can I have some?"
The Gardener: "The harbour gates. Some kind of commotion, I think? I don't follow the local politics." She shrugs. "A Frittte store too."
The Gardener: "We're in Martinaise, sir." She looks around. "This intersection is called... Roundabout North, I think."
Rhetoric: You didn't say she wrote it, you asked what it was doing there.
Authority: Even if she didn't write it, she should CLEAN IT.
The Gardener: "Sir, it was *implied* in your question."
Authority: No! Do *not* keep this random civilian in any loops.
The Gardener: "Snow has nutrients in it -- helps everything green up in the spring. At least that's what my grandma always told me." She smiles shyly.
The Gardener: "Mhmh." She looks at her wheelbarrow, where the snow is slowly melting.
You: "Are you by any chance keeping an eye on us?"
"Are you by any chance keeping an eye on me?"
The Gardener: "Maybe you shouldn't be. I mean... you do your job, but that kid is beyond help. And he certainly won't help *you*." She shakes her head.
Kim Kitsuragi: "We should probably proceed with our business in Martinaise." The lieutenant interrupts her, turning to you. "Unless you didn't have any more *official* questions?"
The Gardener: "If you don't have anything normal to say I had something I needed to think about."
"Do you listen to disco? I need some fresh jams to get out of this rut."
Inland Empire: Psst! Her gloves -- they'll help you with the autopsy.
The Gardener: "Down...?" The gardener straightens her back. "Do you mean the body is finally gone?"
The Gardener: "It felt like springtime just a few days ago..."

"As you already know, there's a corpse there. Hanging from a tree. It smells pretty bad, so I have to take breaks."
The Gardener: "Yes." She looks relieved. "It smells pretty bad, so I have to take breaks."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes. A representative of the harbour. She should have set up operations nearby."
Empathy: She's not okay with it. It's a display of power and she feels threatened by it. You don't know why.
You: "Maybe." (Nod.) "Pleased to meet you, Just A Gardener. I have another question."
The Gardener: "Sure -- I'm done with it." She takes a small capsule out of her breast pocket and hands it to you.
You: Squint your eyes and look at her intently.
Visual Calculus: Are you entirely sure you're black as *fuck*? You should really check out that mirror thing. For now, go with she's black. It's important to the case.
Reaction Speed: Better to get off before it starts. Nothing left to gain here.
The Gardener: "The kid did this, right? The red-haired rat? Can't say a sentence without *f****t* or *kipt*... He's always giving me trouble."
Visual Calculus: She has changed the subject and won't let you get back to this.
The Gardener: "Oh that..." She points north. "That's right there, in the yard."
Perception (Sight): She must be very diligent about the glove-use, because her hands are clean and delicate.
Perception (Sight): I don't know -- what's the problem? You're just *reacting to stimuli*.
The Gardener: "I don't know..." She looks around. "Whatever's on the radio?"
Horrific Necktie: Ask her about music -- it'll get the convo flowing, don't worry!
The Gardener: "I can't believe it's snowing again..." The young woman resting by the wheelbarrow sighs.
"I can't believe it's snowing again..." The young woman watches the falling snow and sighs.
You: "Good to meet you, Just-A-Gardener. Another question then."
The Gardener: "Some shops and a bridge. The canal bridge leads to the coast, but it's broken, I think? Some kind of accident probably."
Perception (Sight): The place looks the part. There's graffito everywhere and the traffic jam behind you is completely *unregulated*.
You: "You could clean it up if you get a chance. Be a citizen -- be a winner."
Kim Kitsuragi: "We should proceed with our business in Martinaise." The lieutenant turns to you.
The Gardener: "Oh... right." She scratches her cheek. "But not from the yard. I understand."
The Gardener: "Uh... I'm gonna say no."
The Gardener: "I'm glad to hear that." A quick smile. "Thank you, officer. Looks like I'll get mint in the ground by April."
The Gardener: "Ask me a normal question or leave me alone."
Empathy: She seems more perplexed than cornered.
The Gardener: "I don't know..." She looks around. "Whatever's on the radio I guess. What does this have to do with snow, or gardening in March?"
Composure: She's a pro. Nothing short of coming face to face with the fatman himself would make her admit it right now.
You: "What is this *fuck the police* business?"
The Gardener: "Excuse me?" She doesn't understand.
The Gardener: "Okay," she replies, shoulders relaxing.
You: "No, the body is down on the ground."
The Gardener: "It was clear just an hour ago..."
The Gardener: "Sure thing." She narrows her eyes.
The Gardener: "It's just water..." She looks at the water, squinting. "No, actually, I think they call it the Martinaise Inlet. There are some islands in the bay, but they're hard to reach."
Perception (Sight): Uhm... are you sure? In the mirror it looked like you were pink, grey and more than a little reddish.
You: "One more thing... Can I borrow your gloves?"
The Gardener: "Thank you." She smiles politely. "My head is about to explode from all the salts I've had to inhale."
The Gardener: "Go easy on that stuff. It gave me a terrible headache."
Drama: She feels interrogated now. It's hard to say if she's lying.
Visual Calculus: That's right. And the canal, the bookstore, the harbour gates... This is a great vantage point -- for keeping an eye on *you*.
Inland Empire: In the West is the miracle...
You: "Evrart confirmed, he sent you to spy on us."
"Evrart confirmed, he sent you to spy on me."
You: "I'm looking for a dead body."
The Gardener: "Oh, that must be the woman on the giant boat." She points northwest. "There's one docked on the pier. It arrived a couple of weeks ago. It's very hard to miss."
Interfacing: If there's a corpse, then you're going to need those gloves for the autopsy.
The Gardener: "Oh?" She cranes her neck. "Well, I didn't write it there. I'm just sitting here."

The Gardener: "What does that mean?" She doesn't flinch.
You: Noted, but I'll keep it to myself.
Suggestion: He didn't think you were about to bust a case.
The Gardener: There's silence. The smallest of smiles.
The Gardener: She shifts in her seat awkwardly.
Conceptualization: What are you waiting for, ask about the disco already. You need some fresh jams to get out of this rut.

The Gardener: "Is that so?" Her face remains expressionless as she shrugs. "I don't know anything about that. Must be a misunderstanding."

Rhetoric: The timidness is gone for a second. Something else takes it's place. A readiness.
